Sociologist William Graham Summer, coined the term ethnocentrism which refers to the tendency to assume that ones own culture and way of life represents the norm, or are superior to all others. conflict theorist point out that ethnocentric value judgements serve to revalue groups, and to deny equal opportunities. functionalist view of ethnocentrism. functionalist point out that ethnocentrism serves to maintain a sense of solidarity by promoting group pride.
